# Axon Project Rules

## Overview

Axon is a tech intelligence feed with three layers:
- **Backend** (`backend/`) — Python, FastAPI, SQLModel, PostgreSQL, Groq AI
- **Frontend** (`fronted/`) — Svelte 5, SvelteKit 2, Tailwind CSS v4, TypeScript
- **CLI** (`Axon_cli/`) — Rich-based terminal interface (legacy, not actively developed)

## Directory Layout

```
backend/app/main.py         → FastAPI routes
backend/app/models.py       → SQLModel schemas (Article, Trend)
backend/app/core/database.py → DB engine and sessions
backend/app/services/fetcher.py  → Data ingestion from all sources
backend/app/services/analyzer.py → Classification, AI insights, chat

fronted/src/routes/+page.svelte       → App shell, all state
fronted/src/lib/api.ts                → API client
fronted/src/lib/ui.ts                 → Navigation config, helpers
fronted/src/lib/components/feed/      → Feed UI (ArticleCard, FeedHeader, FeedPanel)
fronted/src/lib/components/navigation/ → Sidebar + mobile nav
fronted/src/lib/components/reader/    → Reader + chat dock
```

## Article Categories

The analyzer classifies articles into five categories:
- **AI** — Model releases, lab announcements, infrastructure
- **Signal** — Research breakthroughs (ArXiv, academic)
- **Momentum** — Rising projects, expert builds, GitHub trending
- **Discovery** — Usable tools, frameworks, demos
- **Concerns** — Community problems, discourse, debates

## API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| GET | `/articles?limit=100` | List articles |
| GET | `/trends` | Top 10 keywords |
| GET | `/brief/{id}` | Deep brief |
| POST | `/ingest` | Trigger ingestion |
| POST | `/analyze` | Classify + generate insights |
| POST | `/articles/{id}/chat` | Chat about article |
| POST | `/articles/{id}/view` | Track view |

## Data Models

**Article**: id, title, url, source, published_date, content_snippet, insight, category, is_processed, views, likes, engagement_score, last_viewed

**Trend**: id, keyword, count, trend_date

## Environment

Backend reads from `.env`: `DATABASE_URL`, `GROQ_API_KEY`, `GITHUB_TOKEN`
Frontend reads `VITE_API_BASE_URL` (defaults to `http://127.0.0.1:8000`)
